			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1076">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I chuckled when I read Sparrow&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4261">Bananacake</a>&rdquo; [February 2009]. Here I was, on a flight home from a business trip to New York, where I had spent the week talking about washing machines, and here was Sparrow, posing in verse the question: &ldquo;But does anyone / care about my washer &mdash; especially / the sort of person who reads poems?&rdquo;</p>

<p>Well, Sparrow, I can tell you that poetry isn&rsquo;t enjoyed just by teachers in a classroom or struggling artists in coffee shops. It is also enjoyed by business travelers who work for Maytag.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Amanda Konczal<br>Joseph, Michigan</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1077">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Though I enjoyed Sparrow&rsquo;s essay about losing his beloved family rabbit, I feel the need to correct a couple of factual errors. I keep rabbits as house pets, allowing them to run free in my home. Though they chew on everything, my house doesn&rsquo;t smell like a rabbit, as Sparrow fears his would, and they are easy to litter-box train. It&rsquo;s also not true that rabbits will live longer if kept outdoors. They are not well adapted to heat and may become dehydrated and overheat in temperatures above eighty degrees, or lower if they cannot get out of the sun.</p>

<p>More information about keeping rabbits as companion animals is available from the House Rabbit Society, which can also provide information about where to adopt a rescued rabbit if anyone wants to share their home with one of these delightful yet enigmatic creatures.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Charles Wilson<br>Newport News, Virginia</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence-respond fill-pattern-light" id="1078">
								<p><a href="/contributors/sparrow"><strong>Sparrow</strong></a> responds:</p>
							<p>The thought that Maytag employees are reading my sonnets fills me with glee! And let me warn my readers: never take any advice on rabbit care from me.</p>
	</div>


					</div>

